subSubSection.paragraph:
Palp as in Figs 4‒7 , 14‒18 ; tibia with 2 apophyses, ventral (
VTA
) and retrolateral ( RTA ); ventral apophysis with brush of short setae ( Br ) on the tip; RTA longer than VTA , with blunt (not sharply pointed tip). Tegulum with 2 apophyses, massive, hack-like median apophysis ( Ma ) and claw-like prolateral apophysis ( Pa ). Embolus massive, thick, with modified tip (flattened with claw like extension).
